            <!-- Analysis Section -->
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-indigo-900 mb-3">Analysis</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
                Your current draft describes a very specific functional component, a "booking system with calendar integration." While this could be an important feature, it does not define a "full platform for community support." A product definition should articulate the core offering, its primary value proposition, and how it addresses the overarching problem for your target community. This draft is a tactical detail, not a strategic product statement. It completely misses the scope implied by "full platform," and it does not connect to a community element at all.
